    <div class="body">
        <p><a href="http://framework.zend.com/manual/en/zend.currency.usage.html#zend.currency.usage.setformat">http://framework.zend.com/manual/en/â€¦</a></p>

<p>According to Example 8.4:</p>

<pre class="highlight"><code>
$currency-&gt;setFormat(Zend_Currency::USE_NAME&amp;Zend_Currency::RIGHT);
// prints '1.000,00 US Dollar'
echo $currency-&gt;toCurrency(1000);

$currency-&gt;setFormat("American Dollar");
// prints '1.000,00 American Dollar'
echo $currency-&gt;toCurrency(1000);
</code></pre>

<p>This is inaccurate, since setFormat() only takes one array argument, according to v1.5.2 (Currency/Currency.php) beginning from line 223:</p>

<pre class="highlight"><code>
public function setFormat(array $options = array())
{
    $this-&gt;_options = array_merge($this-&gt;_options, $this-&gt;checkOptions($options));
    return $this;
}
</code></pre>

